Amersfort Place, at the S.W. corner of Glenwood Road, showing the Albert Van Brunt house, which was demolished in June 1929; and in the same year, East 27th Street, was cut through the lawn and the Amersfort Hall apartments built on this site. In 1920 it was designated as No. 2700 Glenwood Road.
